@startuml
title Sync staging after a prod merge

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "Local git" as Local
database "origin/main" as Main
database "origin/staging" as Staging

== Before ==

Dev -> Main: PR staging → main (squash-merge)
activate Main
note right of Main
  main advances to a new
  squash SHA (say **B**).
  staging still carries the
  pre-squash commits a1, a2
  — same tree as B, but a
  different parent graph.
end note
deactivate Main

== Sync ==

Dev -> Local: make sync-staging
activate Local
Local -> Main: git fetch origin --prune
Local -> Local: git switch staging\ngit reset --hard origin/main
Local -> Staging: git push --force-with-lease origin staging
activate Staging
note right of Staging
  origin/staging now points
  at the same SHA as
  origin/main (**B**).
end note
deactivate Staging
deactivate Local

== After ==

Dev -> Dev: branch next feature/* from a single tip

@enduml
